\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. Z. tenuior} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 21 (1753). Annual; stems 5-20 (-25) cm, simple or branched, with recurved, short hairs. Leaves on non-flowering shoots 7-25 × 1-6 mm, sparse, linear-lanceolate to lanceolate, acute or acuminate, shortly petiolate, glabrous, often ciliate. Verticillasters many-flowered, distant or crowded, in an oblong, spike-like inflorescence. Bracts like the cauline leaves, ciliate. Calyx 5-7·5 mm, narrowly cylindrical, patent hairy; teeth ovate-triangular, obtuse. Corolla 8-10 mm, the limb usually with a small clavate appendage near the base. Anthers appendiculate.{\i  S.E. Russia, E. Ukraine.} Rs (W, ?K, E). ({\i S.W. & C. Asia.})
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. Z. taurica} Bieb.,{\i  Fl. Taur.-Cauc.}{\b  1}: 414 (1808). Annual; stems up to 30 cm, simple or branched, with recurved hairs. Leaves linear-lanceolate, subacute, petiolate, subglabrous or shortly and sparsely hairy, sometimes ciliate. Verticillasters few-flowered, in a dense or lax, spike-like inflorescence. Bracts like the cauline leaves. Calyx 5-7 mm, narrowly cylindrical, patent-hairy; teeth ovate. Corolla 12-15 mm, the limb with a corniculate appendage near the base. Anthers appendiculate.{\i  Krym.} Rs (K).
\par

\par
 
\pard\f0\fs28   {\b 6. Z. persica} Bunge,{\i  Mém. Acad. Sci. Pétersb.} ser. 7,{\b  21}({\b 1}): 39 (1873). Annual; stems up to 30 cm, simple or branched, with deflexed hairs. Leaves 7-40 × 1-10 mm, sparse, the lowermost ovate, petiolate, the others lanceolate, subsessile, all acute or acuminate, glabrous, the uppermost sometimes ciliate. Verticillasters many-flowered, crowded, in a dense, ovoid to oblong, spike-like inflorescence. Bracts like the cauline leaves but widened at the base, the upper with a few distant teeth. Calyx 7-10 mm, narrowly cylindrical, patent-hairy; teeth narrowly triangular or lanceolate. Corolla 9 mm, the limb usually without appendage. Anthers appendiculate.{\i  Krym} ({\i near Simferopol'}). Rs (K). ({\i S.W. Asia.})
