\pard\f0\fs28 Annual or perennial herbs or dwarf shrubs. Flowers in verticillasters or in lax cymes. Calyx tubular or campanulate, 10(-13)veined, with 5 more or less equal (rarely distinctly unequal) teeth; tube straight, rarely gibbous, more or less hairy in the mouth. Corolla 2-lipped, with straight tube. Stamens shorter than corolla, curved. Style-branches subequal, subulate.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  All species occur in dry, sunny habitats, particularly on cliffs.
